Key Match Events: Pakistan won by 3 wickets (with 7 balls remaining).
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan and Ireland awaited a damp finish in Florida due to washouts on Friday and Saturday.
Both teams were already eliminated from the T20 World Cup, making the match inconsequential for the tournament.
Imad Wasim's final international match was anticipated, with his performances being solid but unspectacular.
Lorcan Tucker had previously scored two half-centuries against Pakistan and had the opportunity to rediscover his form.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in extremely wet conditions in Lauderhill, Florida.
Pakistan's central contracts were up for review at the end of the month, with expected changes.
Ireland had a disappointing tournament despite a promising build-up, including a home win over Pakistan and a victory in a T20 tri-nation series in the Netherlands.
Others: Pakistan may have given Abrar Ahmed and Abbas Afridi a start as they hadn't played in the tournament yet.
The forecast for Sunday was better, but the match depended on the overnight rain and the state of the outfield in the morning.
Pakistan had never been eliminated so early from a T20 World Cup before.
Ireland had lost four successive completed T20 World Cup games, with their worst run being six losses in a row across the 2009, 2010, and 2012 World Cups.
